# GitLab Deployment Pin
#
# Edit this file ONCE on the runner at deployment time. After this file is set,
# the agent never re-derives the host from trigger inputs. The trigger's
# `gitlab_address` is treated as a verification value: if it does not resolve
# to GITLAB_HOST + GITLAB_API_PROTOCOL declared here, the agent aborts the
# operation with a clear error instead of silently switching hosts.
#
# This file is intentionally simple. Do NOT add shell logic — it must be safe
# to `source` from any script.

# Hostname (and port if non-default), as glab expects in --hostname.
# Examples:
#   gitlab.com
#   gitlab-b.pxsemic.tech:30000
GITLAB_HOST=

# API protocol — must be exactly "http" or "https".
GITLAB_API_PROTOCOL=
